Tri Valley Growers (TVG) was a California agricultural cooperative owned by more than 500 member-growers who delivered primarily tomatoes, peaches, pears and olives to the cooperative for processing and marketing. In fiscal year 1998, TVGs sales revenue reached $782 million, and its members equity was $125 million.

As the canning industry faded, Tri-Valley responded with further mergers, purchasing two Turlock canneries owned by the Joan of Arc Company, and S&W Fine Foods in 1978. In 1983, Tri-Valley bought California Canners and Growers. By the mid-1980s Tri-Valley had one Modesto plant for tomatoes and two for peaches, apricots and other fruit.
